    <name>terminal</name>
    <channel>pecl.php.net</channel>
    <summary>Cross-platform terminal helpers for PHP CLI.</summary>
    <description>
        The terminal extension exposes a small cross-platform terminal capability layer for PHP CLI programs.
        It provides backend detection, TTY checks, ANSI capability checks and enablement, terminal size lookup, direct writes to stdout/stderr, raw-mode save/restore helpers, key input, and hidden secret input.
    </description>
    <lead>
        <name>Pratik Bhujel</name>
        <user>prateekbhujel</user>
        <email>prateekbhujelpb@gmail.com</email>
        <active>yes</active>
    </lead>
    <date>2026-06-15</date>
    <version>
        <release>0.4.1</release>
        <api>0.4.1</api>
    </version>
    <stability>
        <release>alpha</release>
        <api>alpha</api>
    </stability>
    <license uri="https://www.php.net/license/3_01.txt">PHP License</license>
    <notes>
        - Added the namespaced OOP API with Terminal\Terminal, Terminal\Backend, Terminal\Stream, and Terminal\Key.
        - Added opaque Terminal\ModeToken raw-mode handles.
        - Added Terminal\Key::Resize and Unix F1-F12 key normalization.
        - Corrected Unix Terminal\Terminal::supportsAnsi() detection order, including NO_COLOR handling.
    </notes>
